"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388108","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-13","<p>As announced at Summer Budget 2015, the government will retain the current duty exemption for small cider producers until and unless a replacement scheme is established.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The UK is discussing reforms to EU law with the EU commission and other Member States, so that it explicitly allows member states to support small cider makers through the duty regime. The government is also looking at alternatives that could apply. The government will work with industry on both of these.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Small cider makers are a traditional part of rural economies who help create a diverse and vibrant cider market and the government is committed to maintaining support for the industry.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","6020 ; 6021","2015-07-13T13:56:57.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388108/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388108/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388108/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-07","Cider: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make it his policy that the tax exemption for cider producers who sell under 70hl per annum remain in force.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","6019"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388109","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-13","<p>As announced at Summer Budget 2015, the government will retain the current duty exemption for small cider producers until and unless a replacement scheme is established.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The UK is discussing reforms to EU law with the EU commission and other Member States, so that it explicitly allows member states to support small cider makers through the duty regime. The government is also looking at alternatives that could apply. The government will work with industry on both of these.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Small cider makers are a traditional part of rural economies who help create a diverse and vibrant cider market and the government is committed to maintaining support for the industry.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","6019 ; 6021","2015-07-13T13:56:57.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388109/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388109/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388109/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-07","Cider: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with his EU counterparts in EU member states on the UK's tax exemption for cider producers who sell under 70hl per annum.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","6020"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388110","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-13","<p>As announced at Summer Budget 2015, the government will retain the current duty exemption for small cider producers until and unless a replacement scheme is established.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The UK is discussing reforms to EU law with the EU commission and other Member States, so that it explicitly allows member states to support small cider makers through the duty regime. The government is also looking at alternatives that could apply. The government will work with industry on both of these.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Small cider makers are a traditional part of rural economies who help create a diverse and vibrant cider market and the government is committed to maintaining support for the industry.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","6019 ; 6020","2015-07-13T13:56:57.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388110/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388110/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388110/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-07","Cider: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect of the tax exemption for cider producers who sell under 70hl per annum on the British cider industry.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","6021"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388111","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-13","<p>The Secretary of State for Transport has asked Sir Peter Hendy, the incoming chairman of Network Rail, to develop proposals by the autumn for how the rail upgrade programme will be carried out.　 Once those proposals have been received, and agreed, the Department will consider whether any specific changes to the schedule of rail upgrades requires further assessment.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-07-13T11:01:12.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388111/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388111/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388111/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-07","Railways: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make an assessment of the impact on the North-West regional economy of the decision to delay the electrification of the TransPennine rail line.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","5884"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388112","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-13","<p>The financial assessment of the impact on the public purse of the agreement with the BBC to take on responsibility for funding over-75s free television licenses was published at the Budget.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-07-13T13:48:25.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388112/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388112/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388112/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-07","Television: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will publish a financial assessment of the effect on the public purse and the BBC agreement announced on 6 July 2015 that the BBC will fund the provision of TV Licences for those age over 75.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","5840"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388113","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-13","<p>The policy for continuation of free television licences for over-75s is set out in the published government and BBC agreement, which says that, at the BBC’s request, the BBC will take responsibility for the policy following this Parliament.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-07-13T13:46:22.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388113/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388113/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388113/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-07","Television: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what his policy is on the continuation of free television licences for people over 75.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","6050"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388114","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-13","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) publish bi-annual statistics on the take-up of the Employment Allowance. In the first year of the Employment Allowance, 2014-15, 89,000 employers in the West Midlands have benefitted. This equates to 90 per cent of eligible employers in the West Midlands.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/employment-allowance-take-up-2014-to-2015-full-year-estimate" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/employment-allowance-take-up-2014-to-2015-full-year-estimate</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>At the Summer Budget 2015 the Chancellor announced the Employment Allowance will be rising from £2,000 to £3,000 from April 2016.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-07-13T13:49:49.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388114/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388114/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388114/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-07","National Insurance Contributions: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent assessment his Department has made of the effect of the employment allowance on businesses in the West Midlands.","false","Biography information for Karen Lumley","Redditch","Karen Lumley","6026"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388115","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-13","<p>As part of building a Northern Powerhouse, the Government is working jointly with Transport for the North to develop options for improved east-west rail journeys in the north. We plan to produce prioritised options by Budget 2016 and expect the first tranche to be ready to inform the Government’s Rail Investment Strategy for the next rail investment period (Control Period 6, 2019 - 2024).</p><p>Electrification of the NorthTrans-Pennine line east of Stalybridge is paused, not stopped, pending receipt of Sir Peter Hendy's re-planning proposals this autumn.  The re-plan will take into consideration the plans for the Northern Powerhouse to ensure we deliver the best solution overall.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-07-13T12:01:45.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388115/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388115/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388115/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-07","Railways: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he expects work to begin on the proposed High Speed 3 railway line; and what assessment he has made of the effect the delay in the electrification of the current TransPennine line on those proposals.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","6024"
